card.name: Tune Warrior
card.description: The warrior's antenna can attune it to any energy wave. It can monitor transmissions from miles away but always suffers from bad reception.

card.name: Water Spirit
card.description: This ancient water spirit haunts the glacial monoliths of Antarctica. It has the power to seep into the pores of any substance and chill it to the bone.

card.name: Axe Raider
card.description: An axe-wielding monster of tremendous strength and agility.

card.name: Dark Blade
card.description: They say he is a dragon-manipulating warrior from the dark world. His attack is tremendous, using his great swords with vicious power.

card.name: Charcoal Inpachi
card.description: A wicked wooden spirit that has burned out. The barbecue grilled with this charcoal is so awesome that everybody thinks it's priceless.

card.name: Woodborg Inpachi
card.description: The new form of the enigmatic Inpachi, remodeled by cutting-edge Dark World technology. Maneuverability has been sacrificed for strong armor, which is considered more important.

card.name: Spiral Serpent
card.description: When huge whirlpools lay cities asunder, it is the hunger of this sea serpent at work. No one has ever escaped its dreaded Spiral Wave to accurately describe the terror they experienced.

card.name: Renge, Gatekeeper of Dark World
card.description: His renowned athletic physique has made him famous with the populace of Dark World. They call him "Iron Wall Renge" because no one can break through his incredible defenses.

card.name: Atlantean Pikeman
card.description: The Great Ocean Lord, who reigns over the depths, is served by these lancers. Deep-sea creatures exist in fear of facing the stream of attacks their lances are capable of.

card.name: Sonic Chick
card.description: Cannot be destroyed by battle with a monster that has 1900 or more ATK.

card.name: Junk Synchron
card.description: When this card is Normal Summoned: You can target 1 Level 2 or lower monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon that target in Defense Position, but it has its effects negated.

card.name: Speed Warrior
card.description: Once per Battle Phase, if this card was Normal Summoned this turn (except during the Damage Step): You can make its ATK become double its original ATK, until the end of the Battle Phase.

card.name: Magna Drago
card.description: If this card inflicts battle damage to your opponent: It gains 200 ATK.

card.name: Frequency Magician
card.description: When this card is Normal Summoned, place 1 Spell Counter on it (max. 1). You can remove 1 Spell Counter from this card to have 1 face-up monster you control gain 500 ATK, until the End Phase.

card.name: Copycat
card.description: If this card is Summoned: Target 1 face-up monster your opponent controls; this card's ATK/DEF become equal to that monster's original ATK/DEF.

card.name: UFO Turtle
card.description: When this card is destroyed by battle and sent to the Graveyard: You can Special Summon 1 FIRE monster with 1500 or less ATK from your Deck, in face-up Attack Position.

card.name: Mystic Tomato
card.description: When this card is destroyed by battle and sent to the GY: You can Special Summon 1 DARK monster with 1500 or less ATK from your Deck, in face-up Attack Position.

card.name: Marauding Captain
card.description: Your opponent cannot target Warrior monsters for attacks, except this one. When this card is Normal Summoned: You can Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower monster from your hand.

card.name: Exiled Force
card.description: You can Tribute this card to target 1 monster on the field; destroy that target.

card.name: Synchro Boost
card.description: The equipped monster gains 500 ATK, and its Level is increased by 1.

card.name: Synchro Blast Wave
card.description: If you control a Synchro Monster: Target 1 monster your opponent controls; destroy that target.

card.name: Synchronized Realm
card.description: Each time you Synchro Summon a Synchro monster, inflict 500 damage to your opponent.

card.name: The Warrior Returning Alive
card.description: Target 1 Warrior-Type monster in your Graveyard; add that target to your hand.

card.name: Smashing Ground
card.description: Destroy the 1 face-up monster your opponent controls that has the highest DEF (your choice, if tied).

card.name: Rush Recklessly
card.description: Target 1 face-up monster on the field; it gains 700 ATK until the end of this turn.

card.name: Monster Reincarnation
card.description: Discard 1 card, then target 1 monster in your GY; add it to your hand.

card.name: Lightning Vortex
card.description: Discard 1 card; destroy all face-up monsters your opponent controls.

card.name: Twister
card.description: Pay 500 LP, then target 1 face-up Spell/Trap on the field; destroy that target.

card.name: Double Summon
card.description: You can conduct 2 Normal Summons/Sets this turn, not just 1.

card.name: Symbols of Duty
card.description: Send 1 Normal Monster you control to the Graveyard, then target 1 monster in either player's Graveyard; Special Summon it, and if you do, equip this card to it. When this card leaves the field, destroy the equipped monster.

card.name: Threatening Roar
card.description: Your opponent cannot declare an attack this turn.

card.name: Scrap-Iron Scarecrow
card.description: When an opponent's monster declares an attack: Target the attacking monster; negate the attack, also, after that, Set this card face-down instead of sending it to the GY.

card.name: Miniaturize
card.description: Activate this card by targeting 1 face-up monster on the field with more than 1000 original ATK that has a Level; its Level is reduced by 1, also it loses 1000 ATK. When that monster leaves the field, destroy this card.

card.name: Spellbinding Circle
card.description: Activate this card by targeting 1 monster your opponent controls; it cannot attack or change its battle position. When that monster is destroyed, destroy this card.

card.name: Backup Soldier
card.description: While there are 5 or more monsters in your Graveyard: Target up to 3 non-Effect Monsters with 1500 or less ATK in your Graveyard; add them to your hand.

card.name: Trap Hole
card.description: When your opponent Normal or Flip Summons 1 monster with 1000 or more ATK: Target that monster; destroy that target.

card.name: Sakuretsu Armor
card.description: When an opponent's monster declares an attack: Target the attacking monster; destroy that target.

card.name: Divine Wrath
card.description: When a monster effect is activated: Discard 1 card; negate the activation, and if you do, destroy that monster.

card.name: Seven Tools of the Bandit
card.description: When a Trap Card is activated: Pay 1000 LP; negate the activation, and if you do, destroy it.

card.name: Birthright
card.description: Activate this card by targeting 1 Normal Monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon that target in face-up Attack Position. When this card leaves the field, destroy that monster. When that monster leaves the field, destroy this card.

card.name: Junk Warrior
card.description: "Junk Synchron" + 1 or more non-Tuner monstersIf this card is Synchro Summoned: It gains ATK equal to the total ATK of all Level 2 or lower monsters you currently control.

card.name: Gaia Knight, the Force of Earth
card.description: 1 Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner monsters

card.name: Colossal Fighter
card.description: 1 Tuner + 1 or more non-Tuner monstersThis card gains 100 ATK for every Warrior-Type monster in any Graveyard. When this card is destroyed by battle and sent to the Graveyard: You can target 1 Warrior-Type monster in either Graveyard; Special Summon that target.
